article.headline: Wagner 87, Quinnipiac 57
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Matt Vitale made five 3-pointers and scored a game-high 20 points to lead Wagner over Quinnipiac 87-57 Monday night, extending the Bobcats losing streak to five. Mark Porter had with 19 points and six assists for the Seahawks (4-15, 3-7 Northeast) while DeEarnest McLemore added 17. Kevin Jolley scored 10 points to lead Quinnipiac (7-11, 3-6), who trailed 37-29 at halftime. Quinnipiac's Rob Monroe, the league's leading scorer and sixth in the nation with a 22.1 average, scored only six points, all from the foul line. He missed all 12 shots from the floor. Wagner, which entered the game shooting 55 percent from the free throw line -- worst in the NEC -- converted 23-of-28 attempts. Jolley's pair of foul shots got Quinnipiac to 56-52 at 9:10 of the second half, but the Seahawks ended the game on a 31-5 tear. McLemore led the way with eight points while Porter and Sean Munson each added seven.
